<section>
  <title><xref ref="S_relations"></xref></title>
  <ul>
    {{ <xref ref="exer_sec71-1"></xref>.}}
    \item
    <ul>
      {{(a)}}
      \item The set  <m>A \times B</m>  contains  nine  ordered pairs.  The set  <m>A \times B</m>  is a relation from  <m>A</m>  to  <m>B</m>  since
      <m>A \times B</m>  is a subset of  <m>A \times B</m>.
    </ul>
  </ul>
  <ul>
    \item
    <ul>
      {{(b)}}
      \item The set  <m>R</m>  is a relation from  <m>A</m>  to  <m>B</m>  since  <m>R \subseteq A \times B</m>.
    </ul>
  </ul>
  <ul>
    \item
    <ul>
      {{(c)}}
      \item <m>\text{ dom} ( R ) = A</m>, <m>\text{ range} ( R ) = \left\{ {p, q} \right\}</m>
    </ul>
  </ul>
  <ul>
    {{ <xref ref="exer_sec71-2"></xref>.}}
    \item
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          The statement is false since <m>\left( c, c \right) \notin R</m>,
          which can be written as <m>c \notrel{R} d</m>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          The statement is true since whenever <m>\left( x, y \right) \in R</m>,
          <m>\left( y, x \right)</m> is also in <m>R</m>.
          That is, whenever <m>x \mathrel{R} y</m>, <m>y\mathrel{R} x</m>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          The statement is false since <m>\left( a, c \right) \in R</m>,
          <m>\left( c, b \right) \in R</m>,
          but <m>\left( a, b \right) \notin R</m>.
          That is, <m>a\mathrel{R} c</m>, <m>c \mathrel{R} b</m>,
          but <m>a \notrel{R} b</m>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          The statement is false since
          <m>\left( a, a \right) \in R</m> and <m>\left( a, c \right) \in R</m>.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </ul>
  <ul>
    {{ <xref ref="exer_sec71-3"></xref>.}}
    \item
    <ul>
      {{(a)}}
      \item The domain of  <m>D</m>  consists of the female citizens of the United States whose mother is a female citizen of the United States.
    </ul>
  </ul>
  <ul>
    \item
    <ul>
      {{(b)}}
      \item The range of  <m>D</m>  consists of those female citizens of the United States who have a daughter that is a female citizen of the United States.
    </ul>
  </ul>
  <ul>
    {{ <xref ref="exer_sec71-4"></xref>.}}
    \item
    <ul>
      {{(a)}}
      \item <m>( {S, T} ) \in R</m> means that <m>S \subseteq T</m>.
    </ul>
  </ul>
  <ul>
    \item
    <ul>
      {{(b)}}
      \item The domain of the subset relation is <m>\mathcal{P} ( U )</m>.
    </ul>
  </ul>
  <ul>
    \item
    <ul>
      {{(c)}}
      \item The range of the subset relation is <m>\mathcal{P} ( U )</m>.
    </ul>
  </ul>
  <ul>
    \item
    <ul>
      {{(d)}}
      \item The relation <m>R</m> is not a function from <m>\mathcal{P} ( U )</m> to
      <m>\mathcal{P} ( U )</m> since any proper subset of <m>U</m> is a subset of more than one subset of <m>U</m>.
    </ul>
  </ul>
  <ul>
    {{ <xref ref="exer_circle-mainmain"></xref>.}}
    \item
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          <m>\left\{ {\left. {x \in \mathbb{R}\,} \right| \left( {x, 6} \right) \in S} \right\} = \left\{ { - 8, 8} \right\}</m>.
          <m>\left\{ {\left. {x \in \mathbb{R}\,} \right| \left( {x, 9} \right) \in S} \right\} = \left\{ { - \sqrt {19} , \sqrt {19} } \right\}</m>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          The domain of the relation <m>S</m> is the closed interval <m>\left[ -10, 10 \right]</m>.
          The range of the relation <m>S</m> is the closed interval <m>\left[ -10, 10 \right]</m>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          The relation <m>S</m> is not a function from
          <m>\mathbb{R}</m> to <m>\mathbb{R}</m>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          The graph of the relation <m>S</m> is the circle of radius 10 whose center is at the origin.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </ul>
